Freddie Ljungberg would be a prime candidate to come in as caretaker with a view to sufficiently impressing to be given the remainder of the season, but the club would consider returning to Manchester City assistant Mikel Arteta. [<br />
@Independent<br />
]<br />
<br />
Also, Max Allegri, Julian Nagelsmann and the former club captain Patrick Vieira.

Wenger on Arteta <br />
<br />
&ldquo;For Arteta, does he have all the qualities to do the job? Yes. He was a leader &amp; he has  passion for the game and he knows the club well. He knows what is important at the club &amp; he was captain of the club. So why not? But whoever they choose I will support.&rdquo;

