<br />
It is understood Gunners would be forced to pay at least &pound;4million in compensation to sack Emery before the end of the season - though his staff would also be entitled to pay-offs which would increase that package. [<br />
@MailSport<br />
]

Arsenal risk losing star duo Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang and Alexandre Lacazette next summer.<br />
<br />
They have been trying to negotiate new deals with the strikers but fears are growing they will be reluctant to commit while Unai Emery remains in charge. [<br />
@MirrorFootball<br />
]<br />
<br />
Even though Arsenal have supported Emery publicly, the club are worried about results with Man City coach Mikel Arteta on their radar while Mauricio Pochettino has been widely touted after being axe by Spurs but would have to cross the North London divide.  [<br />
@MirrorFootball<br />
]<br />
<br />
